With the standard TU social objective, smaller population entails lower near-term carbon prices and therefore results in near-term mitigation cost savings (
 Fig. 2 and 
 
  SI Appendix, Tables S2 and S3
 ). Regional disaggregation for the 2 °C target shows that it is the wealthier regions—those most able to finance sustainable development—that would save the most, in per capita terms (
 
  SI Appendix, Fig. S7
 ). With AU, cost savings occur only in the more distant future. Results with additional population scenarios, robustness checks, and an explanation of the cost savings calculation are available in 
 
  SI Appendix, section 2 and Tables S2 and S3
 ).
